# Optional environment overrides for the substrate.
# Copy to .env to activate. Never commit a real .env file.
#
# Default authentication (no env vars needed): claude-code OAuth-via-
# subscription. The setup script copies your host's
# ~/.claude/.credentials.json into the architect's docker volume; ephemeral
# roles inherit it via a shared volume. This is the expected mode for users
# on Claude Pro / Max / Team plans, and for cloning users running
# 'claude auth login' once after setup. See README.md and brief §4.10.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: API-key authentication (pay-per-token).
# Set this if you prefer to authenticate via the Anthropic API instead of
# OAuth. claude-code accepts ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in lieu of OAuth; when set,
# every container in the substrate will receive it via env. Leave blank or
# remove the line to use OAuth (the default).
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# COMMISSION_HOST / COMMISSION_PORT / COMMISSION_TOKEN are NOT user
# overrides — they are populated per-pair by commission-pair.sh into
# .pairs/.pair-<section>.env and consumed by the planner / coder-daemon
# services in the ephemeral compose project. Do not set them here.
